	abstract = {Subset simulation method, as a technique for structural reliability analysis, can also be applied to engineering optimization problems, such as optimal design, model modification, etc. In order to study the performance of subset simulation optimization (SSO) methods based on different Monte Carlo Markov Chain (MCMC) sampling approach, finite element model updating is used as the optimization background problem to carry out a comparative study on its accuracy and efficiency. The common MCMC sampling methods of standard SSO and subset simulation (SS) are introduced. Based on the above different MCMC sampling SSOs, the finite element model of a cantilever beam with local damage (10 dimensional variables) is performed. The updating results are compared with the model updating method based on genetic algorithm (Genetic Algorithm, GA). Then, the SSO updating methods with different MCMC sampling are applied to the finite element model updating of a four-story steel frame (11 dimensional variables). The results show that the SSO finite element model updating using the random-walking modified Metropolis Hasting algorithm with delayed rejection (MMHDR) and the adaptive conditional sampling (ACS) method has better accuracy and efficiency, and has more advantages applied in the engineering structure finite element model updating problems. © 2023, Editorial Office of Chinese Quarterly of Mechanic. All rights reserved.},
